Make glib's libc-feature probes do real link tests on Emscripten.

The default probes use cc.has_header_symbol() for pthread_getname_np,
pthread_getaffinity_np and pthread_cond_timedwait_relative_np, which
only checks that the function is *declared*. Emscripten's musl-derived
pthread.h declares all of them, but without -sUSE_PTHREADS=1 the
implementations aren't in libc and any call leaves an unresolved
external in the resulting .a archive. That bites downstream consumers
(R, pango, magick) at their final link step.

Switching to cc.has_function() does an actual link test, so on
Emscripten the HAVE_PTHREAD_*_NP macros stay undefined and the
unconditional source uses in gthread-posix.c (currently guarded by
those macros) drop out entirely.

The posix_spawn probe already uses cc.has_function and succeeds on
emscripten -- but glib's gspawn-posix.c also calls posix_spawnp, and
*that* isn't in emscripten libc. Tighten the probe to require both
symbols so HAVE_POSIX_SPAWN turns off on platforms missing
posix_spawnp, and glib falls back to its fork+exec path.

Index: glib-2.84.4/meson.build
===================================================================
--- glib-2.84.4.orig/meson.build
+++ glib-2.84.4/meson.build
@@ -870,7 +870,8 @@ if host_system != 'windows' and cc.has_f
 endif

 # Check that posix_spawn() is usable; must use header
-if cc.has_function('posix_spawn', prefix : '#include <spawn.h>')
+if cc.has_function('posix_spawn', prefix : '#include <spawn.h>') and \
+   cc.has_function('posix_spawnp', prefix : '#include <spawn.h>')
   glib_conf.set('HAVE_POSIX_SPAWN', 1)
 endif

@@ -2134,13 +2135,13 @@ else
   if cc.has_header_symbol('pthread.h', 'pthread_condattr_setclock')
     glib_conf.set('HAVE_PTHREAD_CONDATTR_SETCLOCK', 1)
   endif
-  if cc.has_header_symbol('pthread.h', 'pthread_cond_timedwait_relative_np')
+  if cc.has_function('pthread_cond_timedwait_relative_np', prefix : pthread_prefix, dependencies : thread_dep)
     glib_conf.set('HAVE_PTHREAD_COND_TIMEDWAIT_RELATIVE_NP', 1)
   endif
-  if cc.has_header_symbol('pthread.h', 'pthread_getname_np', prefix : pthread_prefix)
+  if cc.has_function('pthread_getname_np', prefix : pthread_prefix, dependencies : thread_dep)
     glib_conf.set('HAVE_PTHREAD_GETNAME_NP', 1)
   endif
-  if cc.has_header_symbol('pthread.h', 'pthread_getaffinity_np', prefix : pthread_prefix)
+  if cc.has_function('pthread_getaffinity_np', prefix : pthread_prefix, dependencies : thread_dep)
     glib_conf.set('HAVE_PTHREAD_GETAFFINITY_NP', 1)
   endif

